    <note>Zhang(1) Xun [4147] Documentation for descendant, Huan(3) [13664], documentation has his great grandson Xianzhen [13662] moving to Changzhou for the first time, whereas Yu's [325] funerary inscription has Xun holding office in Changzhou and moving here. Since Piling zhi, 7.18b has Xun as prefect of Changzhou during the short period of the kingdom of Wu, I am assuming that Yu's information is correct. Xun is also listed as the great grandfather of Wenzhi [318] and Xun's grandfather, Sheng(2) [12244], as the lineal ancestor of both Wenzhi, Yu, Shou(3) [8017] and Huan. There are some inconsistencies between the various funerary inscriptions of these two branches of the lineage--particularly on when and where they moved between residence in Yangzhou and move to Changzhou, but all agree on the move, and data on Xun and Sheng.</note>
